<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I use this in my init file to separately bind ctrl+i and tab: <code>el (define-key input-decode-map [(control ?i)] [C-i]) (define-key input-decode-map [(control ?I)] [(C-S-i)]) </code> I&#39;m not exactly clear what this snippet is doing, as I copied and modified it from an emacs.stackexchange answer.</p> <p>I tried to use God Mode today, however, pressing <code>i</code> doesn&#39;t activate by keybinding, but that of the tab key. How do I fix this?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Under-Estimated"> /u/Under-Estimated </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w1wou6/god_mode_ci_and_tab_separation/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w1wou6/god_mode_ci_and_tab_separation/">[comments]</a></span>